As part of the She-STEM Internship Programme under the BSCF Future STEM Leaders Programme 2025 Cohort 1, an inspiring session on Women in STEM was conducted by Oishi Jyoti. The session highlighted the significance of equal representation across science, technology, engineering, and mathematics, encouraging participants to break barriers and pursue excellence in their chosen fields. Oishi Jyoti shared personal insights, experiences, and strategies for overcoming challenges faced by women in STEM, emphasizing resilience, leadership, and creativity. The interactive session motivated young participants to develop confidence, ambition, and collaborative skills, while fostering an inclusive mindset essential for modern scientific and professional environments. This initiative reflects the programme’s goal of empowering young minds, nurturing leadership potential, and preparing the next generation of changemakers. Attendees left inspired, equipped with knowledge, and motivated to contribute meaningfully to STEM fields while promoting diversity and equity.
